cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper focuses on visual learning from unlabeled video using a convolutional neural network with a regularizer on tuples of sequential frames. Therefore, it is most likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves machine learning techniques such as slow feature analysis and regularization, which are commonly used in sub-categories such as machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with video datasets, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of neural networks, which is a common technique in the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
